formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1. Because of technical limitation, Amount of estimated Payment of Taxes, cess, fees, charges, premiums, interest etc. to any Statutory Authority under sr. no. 1. b. cannot be changed and hence is without taking into consideration the GST liability pursuant to change in taxability with effect from 1 April 2019.
2. Agreement to sale entered into are subject to verification of registration with appropriate authority, if any.
3. Unit price in case of sold units also includes total consideration received or receivable for the unit which includes amount mentioned in sale deed or agreement to sale and any other amount directly or indirectly received from allotee for the purchase of the property such as Construction agreement, if any.
4. The bank account mentioned in the Form 3 is not RERA account. The developer has not registered with authority a RERA account pursuant to the GujRERA Act.
5. Certain units are further sold in partition to various allottees. In that case sell price and received amount is taken on consolidated basis however name of any one holder is entered dut to technical glitch.
